--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

This role manages powertop.

PowerTOP is a tool that finds the software component(s) that make your computer
use more power than necessary while it is idle.

For more detailed information on the usage and available configuration options
please consult the following sections.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
USAGE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

INSTALL
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: powertop
       powertop_state: 'install'

REMOVE
  - hosts: all
    roles:
     - role: powertop
       powertop_state: 'remove'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
VARIABLES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ROLE
  powertop_state
    Specify predetermined 'powertop_state' variable (string).

    Install: 'true' | 'yes' | 'install'
    Remove : 'false' | 'no' | 'remove'
    Default: 'install'

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DEPENDENCIES
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

PACKAGES
  powertop: >= 2.3
    CentOS, RedHat, Gentoo

